characters.title: Justicar Enforcer
characters.name: Zwei Lanzer
characters.quote: Call me when you need a miracle
characters.lore: A fallen paladin once devoted to the Church of Nirvanis. He was cast out for questioning the Churchs values and now seeks redemption on his own terms. He joined the Guild Vagabonds with the goal of reforming the guild into an instrument of true order, a disciplined arm of justice that hunts the wicked without political constraints.

combatSkills.name: Cleave
combatSkills.description: A large downward slash that splits the earth.

combatSkills.name: Oathbinder
combatSkills.description: A holy burst of light strikes the ground in front of him.

combatSkills.name: Scales of Virtue
combatSkills.description: ATK buff allies.

combatSkills.name: Holy Bulwark
combatSkills.description: Shield buff allies.

combatSkills.name: Heavens Verdict
combatSkills.description: Heaven sword strike.

observations: Has a scar across his left eye.

characters.title: Priestess of the Holy Blade
characters.name: Rei Shirasaki
characters.quote: Let this radiant light purge all that is unholy!
characters.lore: A human Priestess sent by the Church of Nirvannis to join Guild Vagabonds. She is on a mission to banish the Lord of Darkness, who was reported to be unsealed from his tomb after 100 years. She was trained in the art of Holy Weapon, a dangerous skill that can easily sever undeads and demons at the cost of rapidly siphoning life energy to power its blade. Despite having this power, she has a small stature and is very timid, quick to run or mentally shut down if things dont go as planned.

combatSkills.name: Heal
combatSkills.description: Basic healing spell.

combatSkills.name: Smite
combatSkills.description: A blast of holy energy strikes in front of Rei. Strong against demons and undead.

combatSkills.name: Radiant Blades
combatSkills.description: Holy blades appear and slashes enemies in a circle around Rei.

combatSkills.name: Divine Protection
combatSkills.description: A barrier appears and gives a defensive buff to Reis allies.

combatSkills.name: Holy Weapon
combatSkills.description: Holy energy gathers into Reis staff, forming a giant blade made of light.

observations:
Holy Weapon can be casted up to three times, powering up the blade from LV1 to LV3. However, each level past the first one rapidly drains Reis life energy. Prolonged use of Holy Weapon LV3 is fatal.
She makes small dolls of her party members.
She doesnt drink alcohol at parties and feasts but is a lightweight if she does.

characters.title: The Unforgiven
characters.name: Deo Zog
characters.quote: No loss to be given, no path to purify this forsaken land.
characters.lore: An unknown knight who was reduced to naught but a walking corpse. He wanders the lands for reasons no one can fathom. Yet one thing is for certain; none dare cross his path, lest they invite nothing but their own complete and utter destruction.

combatSkills.name: Dark Blast
combatSkills.description: A simple blast of dark energy that deals dark damage.

combatSkills.name: Virtue Sacrificed
combatSkills.description: Consumes HP in exchange for more damage and defense.

combatSkills.name: Agony Blade/Agony Shot
combatSkills.description: Skills change depending on weapons.

combatSkills.name: Laser Charge
combatSkills.description: Charges a laser that goes up to 5 tiers. The longer the charge, the stronger it will become.

combatSkills.name: Transcended Blood Pact
combatSkills.description: All skills change with enhancement.

characters.title: The Restful Wayfarer
characters.name: Ein
characters.quote: A true adventurer knows when to rest
characters.lore: Ein is an adventurer hailing from the village of Eichwald, known for her bright optimism and belief that every journey should be enjoyed. Beneath her easygoing exterior lies a flaw. Once she takes on a task, she insists on doing it flawlessly, sometimes pushing herself past the rest she advocates for. Even so, her thorough preparation and high standards make her reliable and quietly respected by her party members.

combatSkills.name: Stealth
combatSkills.description: Undetectable for a limited duration. Immediately ends if the user takes damage or performs certain actions.

combatSkills.name: Fireball
combatSkills.description: Launches condensed balls of fire towards targets.

combatSkills.name: Detection
combatSkills.description: Sense traps, hostile creatures, and hidden objects within a certain radius.

combatSkills.name: Disarm
combatSkills.description: Disable traps or forcibly remove equipment from a target with a chance.

combatSkills.name: Divine Blessing of Luck
combatSkills.description: Divine safeguard that prevents fatal damage or disastrous outcomes.

characters.observations:
Possess a magic rune dagger that assists fire spells.
Has a magic bag packed with travelling necessities.
To be added

characters.title: Ymir Gorne
characters.name: The Nine Hells Necromancer
characters.quote: Dont worryill bring you back to lifewith or without pain.
characters.lore: A tiefling scholar obsessed with learning the dark arts of magic, for he believes with deeper knowledge comes with deeper power. To go so far to defy religion and the law to obtain power, Ymir finds himself with knowledge even the most skilled sorcerers and wizards don't even dare cast. His experiments are as monstrous as his soul.

combatSkills.name: Magic Short
combatSkills.description: A simple magic short sword.

characters.title: Horned Disaster
characters.name: Erehe Pirestahl
characters.quote: Have you both mettle and metal?!
characters.lore: Erehe occupies most of her time tempering blades in the heart of the mountains. She occasionally descends the mountain to test her forged weapons on random people, caravans and even towns. She simply appears, leaves a trail of destruction and disappears.

characters.title: Malcontent Mercenary
characters.name: Vyshik
characters.quote: My services are worth the price, trust me bro.
characters.lore: Spends most of his time at taverns, people watching and striking up conversations with those he finds interesting. When not on one of his jobs Vyshik is much like your average adventurer. Whether someone is aligned with good or evil, he treats them equally. Once he takes an assignment however, he makes sure to see it through by any means. While he is proficient with lightning magic he uses it sparingly, preferring to get up close and use his enchanted twin blades instead. No task is too much, so see to it you stay out of his way.
characters.crime: 9 counts of Loitering and 7 counts of Littering.
